3. Security Ratings Disclosure Practices 


Notwithstanding these developments, little has changed with respect to most ratings disclosures and regulatory
policies using such ratings. Today, a traditional corporate debt instrument with fixed principal and interest obligations,
a structured note whose principal or interest is tied, for example to an index of securities, an ``interest-only''
